George Alexander Reid (1794 – 12 May 1852) was a British Conservative politician.
Reid was elected Conservative Member of Parliament for Windsor at a by-election in 1845—caused by the death of John Ramsbottom—and held the seat until his own death in 1852.

response: George Reid (1845–1918) was Prime Minister of Australia from 1904–1905.

* George Reid (soldier) (1733–1815), American Revolutionary War general
* George Reid (RAF officer) (1893–1991), World War I flying ace
* George Reid (Victorian politician) (1903–1993), Attorney-General of Victoria
* George Reid (Scottish politician) (born 1939), Presiding Officer of the Scottish Parliament
* George Reid (21st century), British electronic musician and member of AlunaGeorge
* George Reid (moderator) (1692-1763) Moderator of the General Assembly of the Church of Scotland in 1755
